{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/?p=145131", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/04/20/rich-dark-petite-sirah/", "title": "Rich, Dark Petite Sirah", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_1296.jpeg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"480\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_1296.jpeg\" width=\"480\" /></p>Higher elevation vineyard (1200 feet) provides a rich, dark and inky Petite Sirah. &#160;Vines are on a gentle East to West slope with 10x5 spacing. &#160;The fruit has been used in a stand alone varietal but also blending by winemakers. &#160; We are a small family owned vineyard working with an amazing vineyard management firm to ensure excellent fruit for our buying partners.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_1296.jpeg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"480\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_1296.jpeg\" width=\"480\" /></p>Higher elevation vineyard (1200 feet) provides a rich, dark and inky Petite Sirah. &#160;Vines are on a gentle East to West slope with 10x5 spacing. &#160;The fruit has been used in a stand alone varietal but also blending by winemakers. &#160; We are a small family owned vineyard working with an amazing vineyard management firm to ensure excellent fruit for our buying partners.", "published_at": "2026-04-20 19:04:05+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "news_review", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P1_daily_briefing", "P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/?p=145134", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/04/20/petite-verdot/", "title": "Petite Verdot", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/LiZoVineyard-arial-1-scaled.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"1026\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/LiZoVineyard-arial-1-scaled.jpg\" width=\"1600\" /></p>Our Petite Verdot can be a stand alone varietal or used to blend to make a top tier wine for depth and color. &#160;We are a higher elevation vineyard with this block North to South, 7x5 VSP. &#160;We are a small family owned vineyard working with an amazing vineyard management team to ensure every harvest produces high quality fruit. &#160;Looking for other varietals and want one source? &#160;We also sell Petite Sirah, Cabernet Franc and Cabernet Sauvignon. &#160;Contact us for details", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"410\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/LiZoVineyard-arial-1-scaled.jpg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"1026\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/LiZoVineyard-arial-1-scaled.jpg\" width=\"1600\" /></p>Our Petite Verdot can be a stand alone varietal or used to blend to make a top tier wine for depth and color. &#160;We are a higher elevation vineyard with this block North to South, 7x5 VSP. &#160;We are a small family owned vineyard working with an amazing vineyard management team to ensure every harvest produces high quality fruit. &#160;Looking for other varietals and want one source? &#160;We also sell Petite Sirah, Cabernet Franc and Cabernet Sauvignon. &#160;Contact us for details", "published_at": "2026-04-20 19:04:03+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "news_review", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P1_daily_briefing", "P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
{"id": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/?p=145137", "url": "https://wineindustryadvisor.com/2026/04/20/cabernet-franc/", "title": "Cabernet Franc", "summary": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"585\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_2775.jpeg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"585\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_2775.jpeg\" width=\"640\" /></p>Sought after Cabernet Franc fruit from a higher elevation vineyard where exposure is key (1200 feet). &#160;Our fruit produces a dark ruby color. The vines roll down the hill in a North to South slope with a 10x5 quad. &#160; Interested in Napa Cabernet Franc, reach out to us for details as on the 2026 harvest but we will also have another block coming on line in 2027 with no current contracts. &#160; Looking beyond Cabernet Franc? &#160;We can also help you with Petite Sirah, Petite Verdot and Cabernet Sauvignon. &#160;Call or email us for details and a visit.", "content": "<img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"585\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_2775.jpeg\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"640\" /><p><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"585\" src=\"https://wineindustryadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/IMG_2775.jpeg\" width=\"640\" /></p>Sought after Cabernet Franc fruit from a higher elevation vineyard where exposure is key (1200 feet). &#160;Our fruit produces a dark ruby color. The vines roll down the hill in a North to South slope with a 10x5 quad. &#160; Interested in Napa Cabernet Franc, reach out to us for details as on the 2026 harvest but we will also have another block coming on line in 2027 with no current contracts. &#160; Looking beyond Cabernet Franc? &#160;We can also help you with Petite Sirah, Petite Verdot and Cabernet Sauvignon. &#160;Call or email us for details and a visit.", "published_at": "2026-04-20 19:04:02+00:00", "source_name": "Wine Industry Advisor", "source_type": "media", "language": "en", "content_type": "news_review", "country": "US", "continent": "NEW_WORLD", "region": "Americas/North/USA", "producer_role": "trade_media", "trust_tier": "T3_professional", "info_purpose": ["P1_daily_briefing", "P2_market_analysis"], "collection_tier": "C1_rss"}
